    <id="Eartha Kitt">

        <h1>All About Eartha Kitt.</h1>

        <p>A bombshell of a woman, american singer, actress and the infamous Catwoman in the 1960s series <i>Batman</i>.</p>
        <figure id="img-div">
            <img id="image" src="https://hips.hearstapps.com/hmg-prod.s3.amazonaws.com/images/gettyimages-3208729-1560194633.jpg?crop=1.00xw:0.629xh;0,0.0382xh&resize=980:*" alt="Isn't she so wonderful and beautiful? I love this classic photo of her." />
            <hr>
            <figcaption id="img-caption"><strong><h5>1970</h5></strong>
                <p>Kitt did not even know her own birthday until later in life which she is donned in a strapless gown in a portrait shoot that huge and accentuates her beautiful figure.</p>
            </figcaption>
        </figure>
        <section id="tribute info">
            <h4 id="headline">Significances In Eartha Kitt Life:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <strong>1927</strong> - born in North, South Carolina</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1943</strong> - Becoming a member of the Katherine Dunham Company in 1943 remaining in the group and touring until she decided to go solo. Later while in Paris she was a popular nightclub singer. Discovered in Europe by actor-director
                    Orson Welles cast her as Helen of Troy in <i>Dr. Faustus</i>later on in 1950.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1954</strong> - she performed "Monotonus", "Uska Dara", "C'est si bon", and "Santa Baby".</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1960</strong> - Kitt was featured as the infamous Catwoman, which many people loved as the first Black Catwoman after Julie Newmar left in 1967.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1960</strong> - Married John William McDonald.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1961</strong> - Had her first and only child Kitt McDonald.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1968</strong> - There was a huge incident at the White House where she was asked by First Lady Lady Bird Johnson about the Vietnam War she replied: "You send the best of this country off to be shot and maimed. No wonder the
                    kids rebel and take pot." When it was time to ask a question raising her hand politely she answered bluntly;The children of America are not rebelling for no reason. They are not hippies for no reason at all. We don't have what we have
                    on Sunset Blvd. for no reason. They are rebelling against something. There are so many things burning the people of this country, particularly mothers. They feel they are going to raise sons – and I know what it's like, and you have
                    children of your own, Mrs. Johnson – we raise children and send them to war." Which made the first lady burst into tears; at that moment she caused the most
                    <i>horrendous</i> scene at the luncheon. Put because she was Black, outspoken and blunt it caused her to be Blacklisted in the US. She could not get a job anywhere devoting her time overseas in Europe and Asia.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1978</strong> - Kitt rebounds in the US, she appears on Broadway in <i>Timbuktu!</i> and earning a Tony Award nomination for it.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1984</strong> - Actively bouncing back, she made a name for herself again on the music scene once again with <i>"Where Is My Man?</i></li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1991</strong> - She appeared in Ernest Scared Stupid as Old Lady Hackmore.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1995</strong> - Kitt made an appearance in an episode of The Nanny as herself, singing a French song and flirting with Maxwell Sheffield (Charles Shaughnessy).</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>1996</strong> - She appeared on a Celebrity Jeopardy! episode. She also starred in a series of <i>Old Navy</i>advertisements.</li>
                <li>
                    <strong>2000</strong> - Kitt was nominated for a Tony Award in 2000 for her role in Toni Collette's <i>Wild Party.</i></li>
                <li>
                    <strong>2006</strong> - Kitt was diagnosed with bowel cancer in 2006.
                    <li>
                        <strong>2007</strong> - In August 2007, Kitt served as the face of MAC Cosmetics' Smoke Signals collection. For the reason, she re-recorded "Smoke Gets in Your Eyes," which was featured on the MAC website and performed at all MAC
                        stores carrying the set for the month. In 2007, she starred alongside Vanessa Williams in the indie film <i>And Then Came Love</i>.That same year, she won a Daytime Emmy Award for her vocal work on the animated children's series
                        <i>The Emperor's New School</i>, which she repeated in 2007.</li>
                    <li>
                        <strong>2008</strong> - On December 25, 2008, she succumbed to colon cancer.</li>
            </ul>
            <blockquote cite="https://earthakitt.com/kittisms/">
                <p>"Just because you are different doesn't mean you have to be rejected."</p> <cite>-- Eartha Kitt</cite>
            </blockquote>
            <h3>If you have the time, learn more about her and her great accomplishments she has done <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eartha_Kitt" target="_blank">Wikipedia entry</a>.
            </h3>
